{
  "texts": [
    "We further propose future research directions.",
    "These directions highlight the significance of employing various fusion methods and developing trustworthy and explainable AI (XAI) to tackle these challenges and advance AI-driven smart healthcare based on multimodal data analysis.",
    "The motivations driving the implementation of AI applications in healthcare are centered on enhancing patient outcomes, refining diagnostic accuracy, optimizing treatment plans, reducing healthcare expenses, enabling personalized medicine, and facilitating improved resource allocation and management (Ahmed et al. 2020).",
    "The strengths of AI applications in healthcare primarily revolve around enhancing patient outcomes and overall healthcare system efficiency (Müller et al. 2020).",
    "The challenges and weaknesses related to AI applications in the healthcare sector encompass the interpretability of AI models, regulatory hurdles, integration issues with existing healthcare systems, potential biases in algorithms, ethical concerns regarding privacy and consent, and the continuous need for validation and adaptation to ensure clinical relevance and safety."
  ]
}